# 🕹️ ARTIC JUMP 🤻

This is a game written in C++ using the SFML (Simple and Fast Multimedia Library) for graphics and audio.

## 📑🧾Description

This game is a platformer where the player controls a character and tries to avoid obstacles while collecting bonus points and power-ups. The goal is to reach the end of each level while avoiding collisions with fireballs and falling off the platforms.

## 🎴Features

- Player character with movement controls (⬅️left, ➡️right, and ⬆️jump)
- Platform🪴  obstacles that the player must navigate
- Fireballs 🔥 that move across the screen and can cause the player to lose a life if collided with
- Collectible items such as 💖 hearts (which increase the player's lives) and 🪙 gold (which give bonus points)
- 🪜 Multiple levels with increasing difficulty

## Dependencies

- SFML (Simple and Fast Multimedia Library)

## How to Play

1. Use the left and right arrow keys to move the player character.
2. Press the spacebar to make the player character jump.
3. Avoid collisions with fireballs and falling off the platforms.
4. Collect hearts to increase your lives and gold to earn bonus points.
5. Reach the end of each level to progress to the next one.

## How to Build and Run

1. Make sure you have the SFML library installed on your system.
2. Clone this repository to your local machine.
3. Compile the source code using a C++ compiler that supports SFML.
4. Execute the compiled binary to start the game.

